<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--TVCulture     12-12 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--TV Culture,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Culture Minister So Many U.S. Shows On French TV Is Humiliating</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Culture Minister Jack Lang says he's sometimes
humiliated when he can't find anything to watch on the six French
television channels but programs imported from the United States.
   Lang, in a television interview on Sunday, called on the station
chiefs to make their programming ``more French, more European.''
   ``I am sometimes humiliated by the fact that at certain times
there's nothing to watch but American series,'' he said. ``This is
unacceptable. I say to the channel managers: Do your job, serve
French culture.''
   While Lang was speaking on the state-owned FR3 channel Sunday
afternoon, French viewers had the choice of turning to other
stations to watch such U.S.-made programs as ``Magnum P.I.,'' ``The
Incredible Hulk,'' or ``Max Headroom.''
</TEXT>
