<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--ChemicalSpill     12-12 0124</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Chemical Spill,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hundreds Return Home After Chemical Spill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FONTANA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A chemical spill forced about 1,500
residents to flee their homes for three hours, authorities said.
   A 55-gallon drum of the insecticide mercapto spilled at PIE
Trucking company late Saturday, San Bernardino County fire
dispatcher Jo Emery said.
   Authorities could not say how the spill occurred.
   Residents of a section of this city 50 miles east of Los Angeles
were evacuated as a precaution for about three hours, Ms. Emery said.
   Several people who complained of throat irritation and burning
around the mouth were treated at the scene, said Fire Capt. Don
Easton.
   Mercapto can be deadly if ingested or harmful if it comes into
direct skin contact, he said.
</TEXT>
