<1ST_LINE>r i PM-People-Iglesias     12-12 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Iglesias,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iglesias: My Torment With Women</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Spanish pop singer Julio Iglesias says he suffers
from depression caused by hordes of adoring women, a magazine
reported today.
   There are times when he just can't take any more, said the singer
who has dated women like Ursula Andress, Priscilla Presley and Diana
Ross.
   ``Sometimes I just go to my room alone when I've had enough of
all the fans,'' he was quoted as saying by the monthly Woman's
Journal. ``It's then that I have one of my low periods when it's
easy to feel I have nothing.''
   Iglesias 44, doesn't regard himself as good looking.
   ``I'm not handsome and I've got skinny legs,'' he said.
   ``If I had to live only on my looks I wouldn't make any money.
It's perfectly understandable that women are attracted to me because
I'm an artist and I work in showbusiness. All performers get that
response,'' he said.
</TEXT>
