<DOCNO> AP881212-0036 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-88 0230EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Poll-Questions     12-12 0405</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Poll-Questions,0424</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Poll-Christmas, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This Media General-Associated Press poll is based
on telephone interviews conducted Nov. 10-20 with 1,084 adults in
the continental United States.
   The phone numbers were selected randomly by computer, and
interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent
birthday.
   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample.
The poll has a 3 percentage-point margin of error, meaning that if
every adult American were asked the same questions, the results
theoretically would be within 3 points of the poll's results, 19 of
20 times. The error margin is larger for subgroups _ 5 points, for
example, for Southerners.
   Other sources of potential error in polls include the wording and
order of questions.
   The questions and responses in this poll follow; because of
rounding, sums may not total 100:
   1. Do you celebrate Christmas? Yes: 96 percent. No: 5 percent.
   2. Are the Christmas holidays something you look forward to, or
not? Yes: 87. No: 13. Don't know-no answer: 1.
   3. Do you think of Christmas more as a religious occasion, or a
family and social occasion? Religious: 26. Family, social: 34. Both:
38. Neither: 1. DK-NA: 1.
