<HEAD>Two Commuter Trains Collide, Killing Two People</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with two dead, 50 hurt. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger train ran into the back of a commuter
train in south London this morning, killing two people and injuring
at least 50, a British Transport Police spokesman said.
   The collision occurred at the height of the morning rush hour
near the Clapham Junction station, said the spokesman. He spoke
anonymously in keeping with British custom.
   A spokesman for the London Ambulance Service said the crash
occured at the bottom of an embankment, making it difficult to reach
the injured. However, news reports said one train toppled down the
embankment following the collision.
   Three local hospitals have been alerted, said the ambulance
spokesman, also speaking anonymously, and more than 100 firefighters
were at the scene, along with a fleet of ambulances and a mobile
surgical unit.
