churches have been unable to accomplish.'' _ Ernest L. Boyer,
president of the Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of
Teaching, discussing his organization's study that found more than
half of U.S. teachers say they see evidence of child abuse, poor
nutrition and parental neglect in their classrooms.
