   ``There was no looking back, it was just running, running. I
heard the bullets skimming past my head: shoo, shoo. My only thought
was, `I have to hide.' I ran into a Tibetan courtyard. There were
many people there in panic. I said, `I'm wounded,' and I fainted.''
_ Christa Meindersma of Amsterdam, the Netherlands, who was shot in
the left arm, recalling how she and other foreigners were caught in
a clash between Chinese police and nationalists in Tibet in which
troops opened fire without warning.
