<HEAD>Belgian Educator Murdered</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen using silencer-equipped pistols
shot and killed a Belgian teacher in Moslem west Beirut today,
police said.
   They identified the victim as Arthur Van Niewerburgh, an English
teacher at west Beirut's Rashideen School of Languages.
   Niewerburgh, 65, was walking from school to his home in the
Manara district when he was shot by gunmen in a speeding car at 11
a.m., police said.
   ``Four bullets pierced his head. Death was instantaneous,'' said
a police spokesman who cannot be named under standing regulations.
   He said witnesses told police they saw three gunmen in the orange
Volvo used in the assassination. The car did not have licence
plates, police said.
   Niewerburgh's body was still lying in a pool of blood on a Manara
sidewalk two hours after the shooting as police interrogated
witnesses.
   His head was covered with a blood-soaked towel.
   Niewerburgh is survived by a Japanese wife and a 15-year-old son,
Christian.
   His wife, whose name was not immediately available, was abroad on
vacation. She owns the Tokyo Restaurant in west Beirut, police said.
</TEXT>
