<2ND_LINE>PM-Boy Killed,0322</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stray Bullet From Gang Shooting Kills Boy</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Shikita cq in penultimate graf</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 11-year-old boy standing near the Christmas
tree in his living room was killed when a stray bullet apparently
fired by gang members crashed through a window and struck him in the
back, police said today.
   The boy's death Sunday was the second blamed on gangs during the
weekend; a 21-year-old woman who was seven months pregnant died
Saturday after being shot in the head and abdomen. Tammy Harris'
fetus did not survive.
   Authorities were seeking three assailants who drove by the boy's
home in a large car in the community of Willowbrook, 12 miles south
of downtown, sheriff's Deputy Gabe Ramirez said.
   The shooting ``definitely was gang-related, but we do not feel
that this house or this boy was the subject of the shooting,''
sheriff's Sgt. Frank Salerno said.
   The boy, identified as David Polion, was with his mother and
other family members inside their house, about 100 yards from the
shooting scene, when the bullet came through the front window,
Deputy Chris Wahla said.
   ``They heard a number of shots ring out. One of the shots hit him
in the back,'' Wahla said, adding the bullet was believed to be a
stray shot not intended for the house.
   The child's mother, Cynthia Johnson, was ironing her son's
clothes for school when the bullet came through the window past a
recently decorated Christmas tree, said the boy's stepfather,
Vernell Davis, who said he was sleeping at the time of the attack.
   ``We were in the living room dancing,'' said the boy's cousin,
Shikita Roberson. ``He was standing up. We heard a shot. And he ran
to the kitchen and collapsed and began crawling.''
   It was unknown how many shots struck the house. Witnesses said
they heard eight to nine shots fired, Wahla said.
</TEXT>
