<HEAD>Santa Appears From A Military Helicopter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Residents of a town southwest of Tokyo got a double
surprise when a U.S. military helicopter made an emergency landing
with Santa Claus aboard.
   Police said today the Navy helicopter landed Sunday in a rice
paddy about 220 yards from an elementary school after an oil leak
was detected in the rotor.
   One of the four crew members emerged from the helicopter dressed
in a Santa Claus suit in hopes of surprising his family at nearby
Atsugi Naval Base, said the police officer in Isehara, 30 miles
southwest of Tokyo.
   ``(The crew member) said he boarded the helicopter in uniform and
changed while he was aboard,'' said the police official, spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   He said the helicopter was on a routine training flight and no
injuries or damage to the craft were reported. He refused to name
any of the helicopter crew members.
