<FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-88 1602EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Murder-Suicide     12-12 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Murder-Suicide,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Husband Kills Wife, Then Himself With Gun Hidden In Jail Cell</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STANTON, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man arrested after shooting his estranged
wife to death killed himself in a jail holding cell with a gun
hidden in his clothing, police said.
   Morgan A. Patterson, 38, of Crystal, shot his wife, Rosemary E.
Patterson, 34, at her Fenwick home Sunday evening, said Montcalm
County Sheriff Don Godell.
   Witnesses subdued Patterson before deputies arrived, Godell said.
   He was handcuffed and locked in a holding cell at the jail when
he asked two guards if he could use the bathroom, which is in the
same cell and is not enclosed.
   After the guards removed his handcuffs, he turned his back,
pulled a derringer from his clothing and shot himself in the chest,
Godell said. The guards were in the cell at the time. Patterson died
at the jail.
   ``It (the gun) was under his shirt or under his belt,'' he said.
``We don't know exactly where he had that hidden.''
   It was unclear whether deputies or guards searched Patterson
before he was taken to jail, Godell said.
</TEXT>
