<1ST_LINE>r i BC-Lebanon-Text     12-12 0293</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Lebanon-Text,0307</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Text Of Statement Saying U.S. Marine Will Be Executed</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Lebanon-Hostage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of the statement issued
by the Organization of the Oppressed on Earth saying that U.S.
Marine Lt. Col. William R. Higgins will be executed. It was
translated from Arabic by The Associated Press in Beirut:
   In the name of God, ally of the oppressed,
   To the masses of our oppressed people,
   After the grave confessions made by the American spy William
Higgins, head of the so-called United Nations observer group with
the Israel-Lebanon armistice commission,
   And after these confessions matched identically with our
information,
   And after it has been proven by clearcut evidence that he and his
American team of observers are guilty of providing the Zionist enemy
with accurate and detailed military and security information about
our resistance fighters, their positions, movements, supply routes
and the quantity and quality of their weaponry,
   And after the establishment of the existence of intelligence
coordination between the Zionist enemy and some local factions
through Higgins and his American team,
   And in retaliation for repeated Israeli attacks on our people in
occupied Palestine and the Jebel Amel region and the western Bekaa
(south Lebanon),
   And in revenge for the blood of the martyrs of the latest Israeli
raid in Naameh,
   And as punishment for the United States, the head of terrorism in
the world and the foremost backer with arms, funds and political
coverage of the Zionist aggressions,
   Therefore we announce to the oppressed people of the world that
we have issued the irrevocable sentence to execute this American
spy. The spy has been turned over to those responsible for executing
this just and revolutionary verdict.
   The Organizaton of the Oppressed on Earth,
   12@12@1988.
</TEXT>
