<HEAD>Police Kill 6 Poachers Who Slaughtered 10 Elephants</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police shot and killed six poachers who had
slaughtered 10 elephants last week, a newspaper reported Tuesday.
   Coast Provincial Commissioner Simeon Mung'ala said the six opened
fire first during the shootout in Tsavo National Park, according to
the Daily Nation.
   Police recovered 19 elephant tusks from the park, about 220 miles
southeast of Nairobi, he said.
