<TEXT>
   Sonja Henie's icy heart won't be left out in
the cold when the warehouse where it has been stored for nearly 48
years is demolished to make room for a frozen foods plant.
   The blue-green ice sculpture was presented to the famous
Norweigian skater and movie star during a Valentine's Day 1941
performance at the Ak-Sar-Ben Coliseum _ the star's one and only
appearance in Omaha.
