<TEXT>
   Macmillan Inc. has agreed to sell Michie Co.,
which publishes materials for the legal profession, to the Mead
Corp., a paper, forest products and electronic publishing concern,
for about $226.5 million.
   Macmillan said Friday in signing a letter of intent that the
companies hoped to complete the deal before the end of the year.
   It would be the second major asset sale involving Macmillan since
the giant publishing concern was acquired for $2.5 billion in early
November by Maxwell Communication Corp., the British communications
company run by Robert Maxwell.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Electric Co. PLC and Siemens AG said they
would delay their 1.7 billion-pound, or $3.1 billion, joint bid for
the British electronics firm Plessey Co. PLC pending a high court
hearing late next week.
   Plessey obtained a preliminary injunction Friday from the High
Court blocking the offer before a full court hearing on whether the
bid infringes on the anti-competition provisions of the Treaty of
Rome.
