average of 30 industrials rose 1.78 to 2,143.49, closing out the
week with a net gain of 51.21 points.
   The dollar was mixed against the major foreign currencies.
   Bond prices ended mixed in slow trading.
   Sugar futures prices soared to four-month highs; coffee, cattle,
pork, energy and precious-metals futures all gained; and grains and
soybeans were mixed.
