<2ND_LINE>BC-Control Data,0232</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Top Management Changes for Control Data</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLOOMINGTON, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lawrence Perlman, chief operating
officer of Control Data Corp.'s Commercial Credit Corp., has been
appointed president and chief operating officer of Control Data, the
computer company said Monday.
   In addition, Thomas C. Roberts, president of Control Data's
Systems and Services Group, will leave the company ``to pursue other
interests,'' Control Data said. A successor was not immediately
named.
   Perlman takes over presidential duties from Robert M. Price,
chairman and chief executive officer, who has said he wanted to free
himself of responsibility for day-to-day operations and concentrate
on long-range strategy, said company spokesman Frank Ryan.
   The position of chief operating officer had been vacant, Ryan
said.
   In addition, the company also announced that John K. Buckner,
executive vice president and chief financial officer, has been
promoted to vice chairman and retains the title of chief financial
officer.
   Control Data provides computer products and services for
business, scientific and engineering applications worldwide.
   Last month, the company said it may record an earnings loss in
the fourth quarter that ``could nearly equal the profit recorded
through the first nine months of 1988, which would result in
approximately break-even earnings for the year.''
   It attributed the change in earnings' outlook to ``continued
slippages in shipments and acceptances'' in its computer products
division.
