<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WeeklySteel     12-12 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 2.4 Percent in Latest Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.814 million tons in
the week ended Dec. 10, a decrease of 2.4 percent from the previous
week's 1.858 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 84.6 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 86.7 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
93.873 million net tons, an increase of 13.7 percent from the 82.547
million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 88.9 percent of capacity,
compared with 78.1 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Dec. 10: Northeast
Coast, 255,000; Pittsburgh, 200,000; Youngstown, 102,000; Lake Erie,
144,000; Detroit, 205,000; Chicago, 438,000; Midwest, 150,000;
Southern, 229,000; and Western, 91,000.
</TEXT>
